{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "RAAC Homeowners Justice: National Fund, Legislative Reform & Public Inquiry Now!",
        "additional_details": "We think many face bankruptcy and Homelessness after RAAC was found in ex-council homes sold under right-to-buy. We seek a national fund and public inquiry into government and council decisions on RAAC. We want laws to protect homebuyers, including a high-risk building register, mandatory issue reporting by surveyors and solicitors, and developer accountability for defects. We think mortgage interest charges should be banned on condemned properties, and first-time buyer status restored for affected owners.",
        "background": "Support RAAC communities facing homelessness and bankruptcy by:\r\nEstablishing a national fund to aid affected homeowners and tenants\r\nLaunching a public inquiry into council and housing association practices on RAAC\r\nbringing in protective legislation",
